  "description": "Eric Felix Verner Johansson was a high school teacher from Huskvarna. He was born on January 14, 1883, in Ulrika, Östergötland County to J. M. Carls and Mathilda Andersson. He obtained a teaching certificate in elementary school in 1904 and a bachelor's degree from Lund University in 1915. He traveled to Germany and Austria in 1922. He worked as a deputy teacher in Huskvarna from 1912 to 1915 and then became a regular subject teacher there in 1915, teaching subjects like mother tongue, history, social science, and mathematics at Huskvarna secondary school since 1932. He was acting principal in 1932 and 1933."
